you're wrong.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What's your next line of questioning?

choices.string: What have you been doing today?
Can you tell me about anyone else?
What can you tell me about yourself?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I believe I was patrolling the Café. Not necessarily my favorite part of the job.
I’m sorry, I don’t know anyone by that name.
I was at the gym, I’m there daily.
I was doing paperwork in the office. We do a lot of that too, just so you know.
There was a case of Vibro-Shurikens smuggled out of security recently. Josh is our prime suspect, be careful around him.
I’ve seen that kid holding a metal pipe down in the Belly, looking like he’s in some mob film.
People in the Belly somehow get their hands on eSwords every now and then and Josh is definitely one of them. I’m confident he’s not using it for good reasons.
Declaring trust variables based off detective archetype.
Displaying a greeting based off of the trust variable. 1 is the max value
Detective, don’t you have actual criminals to go bother?
Detective.
How can I help you, Detective?
ALIBI SECTION
This is the section where they confirm what weapons they caught other people using.
Guys got a laser on him. It’s legal for people to have them but it’s rare enough for it to cause suspicion. Make sure you don’t scare him.
Reports say he’s selling radioactive ice cubes. That’s why I don’t drink anything with water in it.
I’m not sure if your rank is one I’m supposed to answer to.
What chase?
Maybe I should find them then.
I work security for the world’s biggest security company. Can’t say I always dreamed of being a top tier Mall Cop but the job is fulfilling.
How'd you find that? Must have got it from Mrs. Shi, huh? What a nice women.
[You don't have anything of interest.]
That little…! Sorry ma’am! That perp’s been on my watchlist for what seems like ages now.
I was patrolling the Gym Whitehead area. Seemed pointless though since the place was empty.
What do you want?
Hi.
Oh hey, what's up?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What kind of questioning are we dealing with now?

choices.string: I’ve read your reports from YAP, they’re impressive.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I was at the gym, doing what do you think?
I tried that new extreme caffeine mocha-late grande duplex viente at the Café.
As you might know if you’ve done your job, I’m a member of the YAP. I was at the office filling in some boring papers, as always.
Depends on who.
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Depends on who.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I’m sorry I wasn’t paying attention. Go ask someone else.
You know the security detail got a package of V.S.s lately. What will they use that for, even?
I’ve seen Liam hide a metal pipe away once. Either that was a lost and found item or he has something sketchy going on. Whatever, doesn’t matter to me.
I’ve seen him hold an eSword every now and then. It’s disturbing watching a security guard play with his sword while he’s on duty.
He may be a guard but I saw him once with a laser pistol and like those things are scary. They’re silent and kill people instantly.
I once saw him stash a package of radioactive ice cubes in his pockets. I don’t know where he got them from but I wouldn’t drink anything around him.
Liam is a security guard for the escalator to the Belly. I kinda keep notes on his schedule so I can sneak down there. You seem cool so don’t tell anyone.
Do you honestly think anyone cares?
It was nothing, don’t worry about it.
Well… I joined YAP six months ago, when my GAC scores came home. You know, I get it, it’s a great opportunity but… It’s so much work, you know? I just wanna have fun!
Personal Object ->
O M G, where did you find that?! Please, don’t tell Noel!
[You don't have a personal object to show her]
I know a lot of Josh’s, nothing about their last names, and nothing about them.
I was skipping Noel’s lectures and hanging out by myself in the Café. I made sure no one could recognize me, and I was studying so it’s OK.
Hey.
Yo, wassup D.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: What's your next line of questioning?

choices.string: Can you tell me about someone else?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I was at the gym, working on my sales muscles.
I was at the café, writing my novel. Love, hate, betrayal… It’s gonna be amazing.
Yeah, I was at the office. I’ve got a job too, you know? A legit one and stuff. Everyone has one, so what?
Liam O’Shea? That sounds like a fake name.
She’s bought some V.S.s off me awhile ago. Don’t know what they’re for but it’s a strange order; those things are rare.
I once saw her leave the alleyway with a metal pipe in hand. She told me it was for protection but the way she held it showed experience.
Did you know she has an eSword? She told me she usually keeps it in her room but she once brought it here because she said he needed the protection. It was creepy how well she held it.
She recently bought a laser pistol off me. Those things come at a high price, I don’t know what use she has it though so I won’t ask.
Be careful around her though, she’s been known to hold radioactive ice cubes with her.
I don’t owe you anything, miss detective.
Some people call everything I offer artistic in some way.
Are you trying to make fun of me?

I’m a life-lover, art-breather and respectful citizen who tries to bring some color to this gray world of oppression. I free minds and bodies throughout the ship, and people respect me for that, dude.
Oh yeah, this Carlos guy gave me this in exchange for a new one that allows access to the Fin. Guy’s pretty cool, but he should take better care of this equipment, it’s worth a lot you know?
[You don't have a personal object to show him]
You’d be amazed if you knew the amount of girls I get to know by my job. Nina happens to be one of them, so what?
I was at the Whitehead Gym, trying working on my sales muscles... but no one else was there.
Why are you wasting my time?
I’m a busy man, what do you want?
What can I do for you? Please, make it quick.

choices.string: What can you tell me about other people?
So why are you on the ship?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I don't know what I can tell you about her.
She tends to buy things from this dealer named whatshisface. I think I saw some V.S.s, or Vibro-Shuriken, on her person recently. Hopefully she didn’t have use of them but I’ll let her live her life.
She goes to shady places often, but she can take care of herself. I see her carrying a metal pipe sometimes, it’s way too big for her size but she has a good grip on it.
She has her own eSword that she usually keeps at home. The only times I’ve seen her bring it outside was during show and tell years ago and again recently when she went to the Belly.
I know she a laser pistol recently, but I’m only assuming she has the proper paperwork for it.
She’s been known to carry radioactive ice cubes on her but I like to think that it’s precautionary.
Keep saying that and fail at your job. Does it look like I care?
I know. And I also know what you’re trying to do and it’s not going to happen.
I’m not really allowed to talk about anything that isn’t public, you know. Anything you need to know about me you’ll find in my public profile.
[You don't have a personal object to present to him]
Oh yeah, sometimes the kids think they escaped but I just let them roam around. It’s cute.
I’ve never heard that name, next question.
Ah, Nina. I love that brat. She's one of my students. What has she done this time?
She’s got a nasty habit of bringing her eSword to class. Is there any context where that is appropriate?
Good day to you, Detective.
Good day to you, Jane.
Hello sweetie, it’s nice seeing you again.

choices.string: What can you tell me about other people?
I'll talk to you later, Mrs. Shi.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: Liam is a nice kid, he still frequents this place.
It’s so strange that he’s a guard now. I still see him as a kid, so I actually scolded him recently when I saw him carrying V.S.’s.
He brought a metal pipe here recently, said it was confiscated.
I kicked him out recently when he brought an eSword with him to the shop. Those things are too dangerous to be handled in public.
I still see him as a kid, so it’s strange seeing him wield a laser pistol.
I love the boy but he brought confiscated radioactive ice cubes to my stall recently. Does he know I can lose a ton of business just by having those seen near here?
I take that as a compliment, young lady.
Issit? I’ve always said that if you treat people with respect and care for them that’s what you get back. The snobs from upstairs could learn a thing or two from those in the Belly, lah.
It’s been so long since I got here, and days go by so fast when you’re of a certain age… Thanks for asking, but I’m sure that knowing the life of an old shopkeeper won’t really help your case.
Oh, this is my son with Liam. They were so young back then, good friends too!
[You don't have anything to present to her.]
I’m sorry detective, I get to see so many people throughout the day… My memory isn’t as good as it used to be.
Josh is...umm, I’m sorry I don’t know anyone by that name.
I think Nina visits my shop with her friends every now and then, but I don’t know anything about her I’m sorry.
I’ve known him since he was a kid, which is why I get mad at him when I see him bring his laser pistol here. He shouldn’t carry that thing when not on duty.
Huh? Wha?
Yo.
Amiga!

choices.string: Can you tell me about anyone else?
We can pick this up later.

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Who do you wanna know about?

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: I don’t know many people from the Fin, sorry.
Guy was holding a lot of stuff. The coolest thing was a box of V.S’s.
Guy usually deals in an alley-way so it’s not too uncommon to see him with a metal pipe in hand.
He’s told me that he doesn’t own an eSword but I saw him carrying one once in passing.
I wouldn’t try to rob the guy, he carries a laser pistol on him.
One of the cheapest things he sells is radioactive ice cubes. Why are those cheap? I can’t drink without a second look anymore...
I hope that someone is you, guapa.
Oh, sí mami!
Grew up in the Belly, gained some character. Got a pass to the Fin, gained some money. That’s my life in a nutshell.
Isn’t it amazing that they make such perfect replicas of these things? I think that guy Josh is an artist when it comes to these.
[You don't have anything to show him.]
Are we cool? Idunno yet.
Nah, is she hot?
Uuummmmm…. no (wink). Never bought anything from him, promise! Especially not unregistered passes to the Fin. But he sounds cool.
Josh is cool, just make sure you pay him in full or he’ll hit you with his metal pipe.
